name: FixedOrderComparatorTest
description: Unit tests for the FixedOrderComparator class, focusing on its comparison and behavior with different configurations.

nested_classes.name: Equals
nested_classes.description: Nested class containing tests for the equals method of FixedOrderComparator.

test_cases.name: expectFalseWhenBothComparatorsWithDifferentItems
test_cases.description: Tests that two FixedOrderComparators with different items are not equal.

test_cases.name: expectFalseWhenBothComparatorsWithDifferentUnknownObjectBehavior
test_cases.description: Tests that two FixedOrderComparators with different unknown object behaviors are not equal.

test_cases.name: expectFalseWhenFixedOrderComparatorIsComparedWithNull
test_cases.description: Tests that a FixedOrderComparator is not equal to null.

test_cases.name: expectFalseWhenFixedOrderComparatorIsComparedWithOtherObject
test_cases.description: Tests that a FixedOrderComparator is not equal to an instance of a different class.

test_cases.name: expectFalseWhenOneComparatorIsLocked
test_cases.description: Tests that two FixedOrderComparators are not equal if one is locked and the other is not.

test_cases.name: expectFalseWhenOneComparatorsWithDuplicateItems
test_cases.description: Tests that two FixedOrderComparators with different item counts (due to duplicates) are not equal.

test_cases.name: expectTrueWhenBothComparatorsAreLocked
test_cases.description: Tests that two locked FixedOrderComparators with the same items are equal.

test_cases.name: expectTrueWhenBothComparatorsWithoutAnyItems
test_cases.description: Tests that two FixedOrderComparators without any items are equal.

test_cases.name: expectTrueWhenBothObjectsAreSame
test_cases.description: Tests that a FixedOrderComparator is equal to itself.

test_cases.name: testAddAsEqual
test_cases.description: Tests the addAsEqual method and ensures that added items are treated as equal.

test_cases.name: testArrayConstructor
test_cases.description: Tests the array constructor and ensures that the comparator sorts items in the specified order.

test_cases.name: testConstructorPlusAdd
test_cases.description: Tests the constructor and add method combination and ensures that the comparator sorts items in the specified order.

test_cases.name: testListConstructor
test_cases.description: Tests the list constructor and ensures that the comparator sorts items in the specified order.

test_cases.name: testLock
test_cases.description: Tests the locking behavior of the FixedOrderComparator and ensures that updates are disabled after a comparison is made.

test_cases.name: testUnknownObjectBehavior
test_cases.description: Tests the behavior of the FixedOrderComparator when handling unknown objects with different configurations.
